    <div class="content"><p>I think Cavil made it clear, in his rant at Helen about being made of flesh and bone, that he hated being humanoid because of it's percieved limitations, he hated them, in part, because they had the choice to create him to be stronger, to be able to "See Gamma Rays", etc., and instead put him in a fragile body... In the end you can't really understand him, because he's a fricken nutcase, full of self loathing and jealousy. No doubt they could have done a better job of explaining Cavil during the series, and certainly during "The Plan (or lack there of)", but I don't think it would have ever been explained to anyones satisfaction.</p>
